<!-- From the Titanium Server Admin Guide -->
        <p>The HPE Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade cluster is represented internally by a unique
            object referred to as the <i>system</i> within this document. Information about this
            object is available from the <b>Systems</b> table on the <b>System Inventory</b> page. </p>
        <p><image href="../../../media/CGH-2-inventory-storage.png" width="600"
                id="image_y1l_5vt_ht"/></p>
        <p>By default, the name of the system object is its internal UUID, and it has no
            description. </p>
        <p>To edit the name of the system:<ol>
                <li>
                    <xref href="../Dashboard/CGH-2-User-Dashboard-launch.dita#topic1160c2udl">Launch the
                        HPE Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade Horizon Dashboard</xref>.</li>
                <li><xref href="../Dashboard/CGH-2-User-region-selector.dita#jow1432757989702"
                        >Select the appropriate region and project</xref>.</li>
                <li>Click the <b>Admin</b> dashboard, then the <b>System</b> panel, then the
                        <b>Inventory</b> tab. </li>
                <li>Click the <b>System</b> table. </li>
                <li>Click <b>Edit System</b> to enter a new name and click <b>Save</b></li>
            </ol></p>
